article.headline: Valparaiso 74, Chicago St 66
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Dan Oppland scored 20 points to lead Valparaiso to a 74-66 victory over Chicago State on Tuesday, giving the Crusaders their ninth Mid-Continent Conference championship in the past 10 years. Oppland scored six points in a 9-0 Valparaiso run midway through the first half after Chicago State had opened a 13-5 lead to start the game. Valparaiso (15-12, 11-5 Mid-Continent) led throughout the second half as Chicago State only shot 35 percent for the game. Craig Franklin sparked Chicago State's fast start by scoring nine points in the first six minutes of the game, but ended the game with 16 as he shot only 4-of-13. Oppland added 13 rebounds for the Crusaders, who also had three other double-figured scorers as Joaquim Gomes had 15 points, Jimmie Miles had 14 and Kenny Harris had 10. Rubeen Perry also scored 16 points for Chicago State (11-19, 9-7), who also got 14 points from Jeleel Akindele.
